title: Nietzsche's "The Greek State" - Part 4 Finale - "Fatalism, Fate, War, Civil War"
description:
Today we continue discussing Nietzsche's "The Greek State" - the finale and finality of fate, fatalism, war, and civil war.  Or. Eternal recurrence. 

For clarity sake regarding the title:  "Civil war" only means "internally derived destruction, or decomposition of the state (and its property, or, people)."  Civil war isn't just physical violence, and is never the same as any "civil war" of any single nation's past, but as Thucydides writes, it's when the State, therefor, the culture, therefor the people's words and Values change.  The very "meaning (and Values) of everything" is split.  What then is the biggest difference between the Greek State, and all states who have imitated them since?  

The Greeks weren't "trying to do/fix/save" anyone or anything.  They were simply being themselves - murderous and powerful.  The problem with Western History since the original Greeks died off is, since the Platonic and then Christian ideal, the imitation Greek State then lies to everyone that it has any objective (justice, equality, etc) other than Power. There is no goal, purpose, or meaning to existence, and as pertains to the state and the individual subject of it, in some sense, they were never meant to have a mind, being, or "freedom" of their own.  They were supposed to be asleep to life as a dream - that the larger species forever falls asleep and wakes up to this.  What is then felt and compelled?  The greed and need of life - a race against time - but to arrive where?  The end.

title: David Foster Wallace‚Äôs ‚ÄúE Unibus Pluram‚Äù ‚Äì Irony is Tyranny Pt. 5 Reaping Perpetual Destruction
description:
All species and their members eventually die, or change into something else.  In trying to deny and tyrannize this "bad ending" (death, reality, living and dying in the 'natural world' as real human beings) - Western Christian humanity have fabricated a corporate consumer party who leaches, enslaves, and destroys life far more than they "create, foster, nurture, and tend to life," despite slogans to the contrary, and despite modern industry ‚Äúproducing‚Äù an historically unprecedented surplus (largely of and for destruction in perpetual war) through the labor of masses of slaves and wage-slaves the world over, all of which serves one purpose and one purpose alone:  to fund the mono-state's perpetual war of destruction and control.  The irony isn't just that this corporation-state-death-cult lies to the world and one another's face, and says it serves life, "is the good guy," but that it is in fact the most rapacious and destructive force in human history (capitalism is imitation of repetition, not creation, and on someone else's time and dime too; basic reptiles never had it so easy or good). What does irony really say then, as youthful rebellious attitudes designed and sold for decades in commercial advertising; redundant "art" and gibberish written by backwards generations of already-backwards Americans in daycares that pass for colleges; and a political body and language that has been regurgitated by a corporate-political machine for decades, all of which is informed by what was stolen from better men, art, literature, philosophy, and psychology?  American irony is a big middle finger, a collapsing into prostration of death worship, a wallowing in and crying over being a prisoner in a vast human abyss, and ultimately, it is a demented salute and cheer of the damned, the annihilation of the self, since the self cannot or Will not ever say what it means, or do what it wants. Irony in the United States real subtext is, then, "nobody cares, everybody is a slave to something and somebody else, and nobody can do anything about it," not even the actors who pretend to be leaders. This cult of nihilistic death worship set the bar, lowered the bar, is the model, and ensures that all species, and the Earth's three super-powers and their denizens, get the worst ending, forever.  In the meantime, liberalism serves to turn mankind into cattle, what psychologist Dr. Erich Fromm calls an obsessive worship of death (objects and parts and their destruction), which is to say, an enjoyment in the happy cannibalism of maliciously subjugating life and eating it; the detachment of emotions and the belief in a statistical and mechanical reality; a worship of objects and paper; an inability to use or create language - not to name and create, but repeat words and think that is the same as "knowing" or "wisdom"; all of which Fromm describes as a compensation and a 'destructiveness of "necrophilia."  In America, this mindless, prefabricated hedonic treadmill of imitation, repetition and consumption, and the destruction/subjugation of life, is generally called "success," driven by the lust for power called "progressivism" created by a recently fabricated and half-assed system that functions by defusing and refusing all responsibility, resembling all of Kafka's worst insectoid-circus nightmares. This system of fatally-ironic death-worship goes by its own names (has its own values, morality) in Eurasia and Eastasia, but in soulless and destructive industrial terms - it rules where man is object and life is statistics and paper.  Which is to say, the truth of life and perpetual war in the other two super powers is much the same. There is one party - the state - it only knows perpetual war and dissimulation, and its province, principle, and aim is controlling life and propagating necrophiliac values, including the assimilation and destruction of people, art, and an imitation ‚Äúculture‚Äù and its tyrannical corporate language.
